DimLocation
Description: Geographic hierarchy and socioeconomic context
Field NameData TypeDescriptionExampleLocation_KeyIntegerUnique identifier (primary key)15RegionTextUK regionNorth EastLocal_AuthorityTextCouncil/local authority nameNewcastleDeprivation_DecileIntegerArea deprivation ranking2
Records: 44 (unique local authorities)
Regions Included:

North East, North West, Yorkshire, West Midlands, East Midlands
East, London, South East, South West, Wales, Scotland

Deprivation Context:

Decile 1-3: High deprivation (frequent food bank use)
Decile 4-7: Moderate deprivation
Decile 8-10: Low deprivation (rare food bank use)


DimReferral
Description: Referral source categories
Field NameData TypeDescriptionExampleReferral_KeyIntegerUnique identifier (primary key)3Referral_SourceTextOrganization/source that referred familyJobcentre Plus
Records: 8
Referral Sources:

Jobcentre Plus (unemployment services) - ~35% of referrals
Social Services - ~20%
School/College - ~12%
Health Services - ~10%
Housing Services - ~8%
Self Referral - ~7%
Citizens Advice - ~5%
Unknown - ~5% (missing data)


Data Quality Notes
Missing Values

Referral_Source: 5% of records (handled as "Unknown" category)
All other fields: 0% missing (complete data)

Data Validation Rules

Total_Parcels = Children_Parcels + Adult_Parcels (enforced)
Date range: 2021-01-01 to 2024-12-31 (no outliers)
Deprivation_Decile: Integer 1-10 only (validated against ONS)

Known Limitations

Monthly grain (daily detail not available)
No household-level tracking (privacy protection)
Population data from 2019 census (static, not annually updated)
Simulated data for portfolio purposes (patterns based on real trends)


Calculation Definitions
Key Metrics
Per-Capita Rate:
Parcels Per 1000 Population = (Total Parcels / Population in 1000s)
Normalizes demand by area size for fair comparison
Year-over-Year Growth:
YoY Growth % = ((Current Year - Previous Year) / Previous Year) × 100
Measures demand change vs same period last year
Seasonal Index:
Winter months = December, January, February
Seasonal spike = (Winter Average - Annual Average) / Annual Average
Quantifies winter demand increase

Business Glossary
TermDefinitionFood ParcelEmergency food provision (typically 3 days' worth of nutritionally balanced food)ReferralOfficial recommendation from authorized agency for family to receive food bank supportDeprivation DecileUK government ranking of area poverty (1=poorest, 10=wealthiest)Local AuthorityUK council/government district (e.g., Newcastle City Council)Emergency SupportShort-term food provision during crisis (job loss, benefit delay, unexpected expense)

Source Data Provenance
Original Source: FoodReach UK Operations Database (Simulated)
Extraction Date: January 2025
Refresh Frequency: Monthly (real-world deployment)
Data Steward: Operations Team
Data Classification: Public (anonymized, no personal identifiers)

